The paper deals with the closure properties of languages defined by deterministic reversal-bounded multi-counter machines, which are typically studied in the formal language theory (cs.FL) and automata theory (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deletion operations, which are relevant to the study of regular languages (cs.FL) and context-free languages (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper explores the properties of left and right quotients, which are relevant to the study of algebraic structures (cs.AL) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of certain types of machines, which is relevant to the study of computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO).
